    About the Business

    A2Z Remodeling is considered to be one of the best general contractors in the bay are of San Franciscan. We specialize in full home renovations, home additions & expansions, decks, bathroom remodels, kitchen remodel, flooring, rewire, repipe, drywall & paint. serving the bay area of San Francisco including the Peninsula, Silicone Valley, Oakland, San Jose, Livermore & Dublin area, San Ramon, Danville, Danville, Walnut Creek, Palo Alto, Atherton, San Carlos and many more

      Just finished a full bathroom remodel with A2Z and I HIGHLY recommend! I'd give 10 stars if I could. Everyone I have interacted with at this company is spectacular.

      This was my first remodel ever- I anticipated that it would be challenging, endlessly delayed, and way way way over budget. I am so happy to report that my experience with A2Z was basically the exact opposite of this :)

      Dor (my project manager) was lovely to work with from the get-go. He has a quiet competence about him, and is extremely knowledgable about every step of the process (i.e. he answered all 28,745 of my questions). Aside from being great at his job he's also just a cool guy that is fun to work with. He is also very responsive via text and email, which is so important!

      Once the renovation got started, it became clear that Dor's team is just as awesome as he is. The foreman (Augustine) and his team were so talented AND somehow so fast. Every 1-2 days I would drop by to check on the progress and frequently found myself thinking "wow this looks great!" but also "omg this is really moving along super quickly."

      Worth noting that during the demo, we ended up running into some water damage. Dor handled both the situation (repairing the damage) and me (I was freaking out about the water damage) very well. It ended up not delaying the project at all, and we ended up finishing *way* ahead of schedule.

      I also appreciated that he had the same team there for the whole project! This gave me (single gal living alone) a sense of familiarity/ security, but was also helpful for my condo neighbors to not feel like there were random strangers around all the time.

      Regarding pricing, A2Z is very fairly priced for what's included, the service level, and the quality of work that is delivered. The price of the work was fixed, there were zero unexplained/ mystery charges. If something had to be adjusted (additional work I requested specifically, water damage previously mentioned), it was communicated clearly and in advance.

      I would pick Dor/ A2Z Remodeling again in a heartbeat, and will be recommending these guys to everyone I know!

      Trusting A2Z Remodeling with our kitchen and bathroom remodel was the best decision we ever made! Our 6-month-long remodel was quite extensive with the removal of a load-bearing wall, combining rooms, a completely new layout, relocating doors and windows, the laundry, etc. The results are outstanding and we couldn't be any happier!

      At first, we were hesitant about remodeling during the pandemic, given that we are both working from home and have children. We met several contractors. Most of them told us that they partner with other subcontractors which add a lot of unknowns to the timeline and final price.
      When we met Dror Postiner, he made us immediately feel like we are in good hands. From the beginning, we were impressed by his honesty and integrity. He also made a couple of great design suggestions during his first walkthrough. We felt that he'd be a great partner for this project.

      Why we loved working with A2Z Remodeling:
      1. Fixed price: A2Z prices tend to be a bit higher but after talking to others, we came to believe that other contractors often don't quote the full price upfront and successively come up with additional expenses. With A2Z, we ended up paying what they quoted us, not more.
      2. Flawless project management, full service: A2Z did their name justice and managed everything from start to finish. Including structural assessment, plans, permits, inspections, electrical, plumbing, flooring, walls, framing, etc. -- all of this in time and within budget. Everything was taken care of, we didn't have to drive anything. We didn't have any unexpected outcomes or bad surprises.
      3. Reliability: The crew was amazing! Punctual, polite, respectful, clean, and considerate of us, our kids, and our pets. A2Z made sure to vacuum everything every single day before they left in the evening. They always cleaned up their tools and closed access to anything potentially dangerous.
      4. Communication: We had a group chat with Dror. We texted several times a day. Dror made sure that we are always up to date with the progress and told us in time when there was action required on our end.
      5. Quality & Design: The quality of the work speaks for itself. All members of the A2Z team were stellar in their job. They never took shortcuts, always involved us where there were options, and went for the best solution as if it would be their own home. We designed our kitchen and bathroom ourselves but didn't exactly know what can be done and what cannot be done. Dror and his crew were perfect partners for walking us through the possibilities. Together, we figured out every single detail and the results are stunning.

      We couldn't be happier with the result! The kitchen and the bathroom turned out exactly the way we wanted. We will certainly hire A2Z again in the future and would highly recommend them to anyone!
